THE regional auditions of the Hi-Life Fest 2019 has been concluded in Aba, Abia State, wrapping up a series of events which occurred over the last few weeks. Kicking off on June 2, 2019, the regional knockouts saw various highlife talents emerge, and the final round of auditions in Aba capped-off an amazing four weeks of performances. The Aba auditions saw artistes show their musical talents in hopes of earning a place in the quarter-final. At the end of the event, Chimaroke Chimex and Umunnakwe Nwajiakor emerged as the top two contestants in the singing category, while Megastar Dance Group emerged victorious in the dance category. With the regional knockouts now concluded, the contestants will head to Lagos for mentorship, where they will learn the ropes and rudiments of the music industry from successful artistes and producers in the Nigerian music scene. The winner of the 2019 Hi-Life FEST is set to earn a whopping sum of N5 million while the first and second  runner-ups will also go home with N2 million and N1 million respectively. This year’s edition which is themed ‘Rhythm of Progress’, is the third edition of the talent hunt show and is the first to be televised across Africa. Episodes of the show are  aired every Sunday at 8pm on Soundcity. Hi-Life FEST is an initiative of Life Continental Lager Beer, from the stables of Nigerian Breweries Plc.